In `onItemSelected` you could do something like this after your log statement. Check if the view is of type spinner and if so set the selection to the index of the position you clicked.

```
if(view instanceof Spinner) {
  (Spinner)view.setSelection(position);
}
```
If your `onItemSelected` is only used by your spinner, you could take all the code out of `onItemSelected` and set the onClickListener directly for your spinner, that way the `instanceof` check isnt needed.

It should work out of box. I think there is an issue with emulator, or old dependency in the project. Validate on real device too. **There might be alternatives, which I don&#39;t like too!** 

